01]]\n|update = Dragon quest online!\n|members = No\n|combat = 43\n|size = 1\n|examine = He looks totally insane!\n|xpbonus = 0\n|max hit = 5\n|aggressive = Yes\n|poisonous = No\n|attack style = [[Magic]], [[Crush]]\n|attack speed = 4\n|slayxp = N/A\n|hitpoints = 44\n|att = 37\n|str = 37\n|def = 34\n|mage = 40\n|range = 1\n|attbns = 0\n|strbns = 0\n|amagic = 0\n|mbns = 0\n|arange = 0\n|rngbns = 0\n|dstab = 0\n|dslash = 0\n|dcrush = 0\n|dmagic = 0\n|drange = 0\n|immunepoison = Immune\n|immunevenom = Immune\n|respawn = 30\n|id = 823\n|immunecannon = No\n|immunethrall = No\n}}\n[[File:Melzar the Mad chathead.png|left]]\n'''Melzar the Mad''' is one of the three wizards, along with [[Thalzar]] and [[Lozar]], who escaped from [[Crandor]] when the [[Dragon (race)|dragon]] [[Elvarg]] destroyed it, and is the only one of them to have survived. He has since lost his sanity, leading to his nickname, and has secluded himself and his [[Map parts|piece of the map to Crandor]] in [[Melzar's Maze|his maze]] north-west of [[Rimmington]]. He is fought during the [[Dragon Slayer I]] quest.\n\nIn combat, Melzar can kick, punch, cast [[Fire Strike]] or a [[Curse spells|Curse spell]], or cast a [[spell]] that produces a [[cabbage]] in a random spot in the room. (Note that the cabbages '''CAN''' be used for [[food]].)\n\n==Location==\n{{LocTableHead}}\n{{LocLine\n|name = Melzar the Mad\n|location = [[Melzar's Maze]] Basement\n|levels = 43\n|members = No\n|mapID = 3\n|plane = 0\n|x:2929,y:9649\n|mtype = pin\n}}\n{{LocTableBottom}}\n\n==Quotes==\nBecause Melzar the Mad is insane, while fighting, he says things that don't make sense.\n*Feel the wrath of my feet!\n*Let me drink my tea in peace.\n*By the power of custard!\n*Leave me alone, I need to feed my pet rock.\n\n==Changes==\n{{Subject changes header}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 18 June 2007\n|update = The Dragonfire Shield\n|change = The NPC was renamed from \"Melzar the mad\" to \"Melzar the Mad\".\n}}\n{{Subject changes footer}}\n\n